<br>
I went to BG1 for the first time today, at level 20.  I only got to fight primarily red enemy tanks and I got rocked <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   A Reaver was hitting me for 50-100 dmg and I was hitting back for 20-30.  I also ran into a Hero and he dropped me even faster than the Reaver did.  Just curious, does it get any better for us?  If I was even levels to them so they were yellow should things have gone better for me?  I don't mind getting beat down now and then, but my Savage's performance seemed really bad. <br>
<br>
My armor is all yellow to me, weapons are enchanted and yellow to me.  My current specs are Hand to Hand 18 +3, Savagery 15, Parry 5 +1.  Any suggestions or experiences others have had are appreciated.  I wasn't really sure what my goals should be, charge casters, etc?   So far I have only played healers or pure casters in RvR, so am not used to it at all from a tanks perspective. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> sindux</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(1/20/03 4:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Savages in RvR</span><hr size=1> I was wondering if anyone could tell me how our HTH weapon styles do in RvR.  The AOE affect does not seem particularly useful to me.  Sure the 44 and 50 spec both let you hit 3 and 4 targets but, how often am I doing to be attacked by 4 targets and get to the 4th style in a chain (this is what the 50 spec gets you).  If by some freek chance I do get this style off how in the heck to I kill them to get the RP?<br>
<br>
Maybe the intent was for you to be fighting a tank who is standing right next to 3 casters who happen to be targeting some other foe.  I just don't understand how AOE with a radus of 350 is useful in RvR.  But I would like to know from some of you who are 50 and had a chance to try this out.  I am Currently 39 and will stop specing my HtH and just use Items to get me to 50 unless someone out there can clerify this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=degrix>Degrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(1/29/03 8:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savages in RvR</span><hr size=1> An AoE of 350 is identical to that off all the PBAoE casters out there who have even less hp then we do.  I think the idea was just as you mentioned, find the designated caster guard and whack him (a cleric or druid perhaps, just by chance standing near the other casters).  The radius of 350 would allow you to at the very least disrupt all the casters in the general vicinity, which, if coordinated correctly, should be more then enough time to finish off your prey before either getting blasted into oblivion, or allowing your partners in crime the ample time they need to finish up their targets and come aid you in killing the other casters. <p>Octavius Goodfellow<br>
The Iron Throne (Palomides)<br>
<br>
~Before God we are all equally foolish~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hauv>Hauv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(2/4/03 10:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savages in RvR</span><hr size=1> The 44 style does more then just hit 4 targets. It also stuns for 9 seconds which is why alot go to at least 44 in HtH. The stun is nice.<br>
<br>
The AOE debuff is usefull if you have more then one person beating on you. You can slow em all down at the same type thus allowing your healer to heal you better.<br>
<br>
The back positional and the side positonal are your bread  and butte rin rvr. Followed up by Wild Call our taunt. Because without an anytime style we have to improvise a bit. A wild call works out really well with its high bones to damage. Of course if you evade always go into the totemic combo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=32.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=32.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.threadControl?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of rep